    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="1151"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1151">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 840.48/979</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Austria-Hungary</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PFC1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Penfield</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Vienna</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-24">
                        <hi rend="italic">November 24, 1914</hi>.</date>
                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received November 26, 8 p.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>305. Can passports issue and financially assist return children of tender years
                    born in United States (1) of parents not naturalized, (2) of declarants?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PFC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Penfield</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <pb facs="1042" n="728" xml:id="pg_728"/>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Ambassador in Austria-Hungary</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PFC1"
                            type="to">
                            <hi rend="italic">Penfield</hi>
                        </persName>)</head>
                    <note rend="inline" rendition="#center">[Telegram]</note>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-03">
                                <hi rend="italic">December 3, 1914</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>327. Your 305, 24th. Passports and financial assistance may be extended to
                        American-born minor children of parents not naturalized or declarants.</p>
                    <p rend="right">
                        <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </p>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
        </body>
